論文基本資料
摘要
外文摘要
紙本論文
QR Code



本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:王素貞研究生(外文):Wang, Su-chen論文名稱:台語會話中的語調單位及語調下降單位論文名稱(外文):Intonation Units and Declination Units in Taiwanese Discourse指導教授:江文瑜指導教授(外文):Wen-yu Chiang學位類別:碩士校院名稱:國立臺灣大學系所名稱:語言學研究所學門:人文學門學類:語言學類論文出版年:1998畢業學年度:86語文別:英文論文頁數:197中文關鍵詞:語調、韻律、韻律單位、韻律特徵外文關鍵詞:Intonation、Prosody、Prosodic units、Prosodic features相關次數:

被引用:0點閱:189評分:下載:0書目收藏:1



               摘要               本研究主要是以聲學的實驗方式來探討閩南語會話中的 二種韻律單位(prosodic               units) --- 語調單位 (intonation units or IUs)及語調下降單位 (declination               units or DUs)。雖然這二種單位 皆屬於語調的範疇，然而前人對於他們的研究顯少               觸及其聲學特質，更遑論比較不同韻律成份 (prosodic constituent) 的語調特性。               因此本研究的課題之一即是運用實驗語音學的方式來探討語調單位和語調下降單位的韻               律特徵(prosodic features)，藉以驗証前人對語調單位所提出的定義在聲學上是否               有效，進而比較這二種單位的特性。此外，我們也進行了二個實驗來討論不同轉註者               (transcriber) 在切分語調單位上的一致性有多高，進而藉由語調單位的韻律特性               來解釋不同轉註 者(transcriber)在切分語調單位上為何會有部份歧異性。                   本研究收集了二則會話，共26分鐘，其中第一則會話是為二個實驗的語料。這二個               實驗的結果顯示，說話者在 每個語調單位的一開端會加快說話速度，但是到了其末尾               時，說話速度減慢，甚至有句末尾音拉長的現象 (final lengthening)，接著有時               會停頓一會兒，再開始下一個單位；除了說話節奏 (tempo) 轉變外， 語調單位同時               也有音高上的變化，包括語調下降 (declination) 及語調重新提高 (resetting)。               在第一個實驗，轉註相同的語調單位數低於全部的百分之七十，因而我們進而檢驗兩               個可能造成 如此低比率的原因 --- 個人差異及各各語調信號 (cue) 之間的相對重               要性。結果顯示其中一位轉註者較看重停頓 (pause)，而另一位則較依賴句首語音加快               (anacrusis)；另一結果顯示，當停頓及句末語音拉長的信號不夠明顯時 ，不同的轉註               者容易有不同的分割 (segment)。此二項結果 都一致性地指出時間 (timing) 是造成               切分台語語調單位的 困難及歧異產生的主要因素。                   會話中的語調下降單位(DUs)同樣也呈現與時長有關的韻律 特徵，單位前的停 頓               (pause) 長於單位內的停頓，同時句未語音拉長 (final lengthening) 及句首語音               加快 (anacrusis) 亦是語調下降單位的特性。此外，語調下降單位同樣具有語調下               降(declination)及語調重新提高 (resetting) 的聲學特質。雖然語調單位及 語調下               降單位 有相同的韻律特徵(prosodic features)，但是這些特徵 在這兩種單位的 強度               表現不一樣，語調下降單位的語調下降及語調重新提高都比語調單位來得強，此外，語               調 下降單位前的停頓會長於語調單位前的停頓。在 336 個語調下降單位，有 70%               以上的簡單子句 (simple clause) 及複雜子句(clause-complex)；而語 調單位最多只               是簡單子句。平均而言，語料顯示 2 個連續性的語調單位構成一個語調下降單位，而               每個語調下降單位包函 11.58 個音節。然而，也有 38.39% 的語調下降單位 僅包函               一個語調單位。                   鑑於語調下降單位通常是由二個至三個連續性的語調單位所組成，而說話者在表達               一個簡單子句或複雜子句時，其語調單位如何流出湧入即成為一個有趣的問題。結果               顯示，第一個語調單位的音節數會比最 後一個語調單位來得少，而總長來得短，換言               之，第 一個語調單位的訊息會比最後一個來得少。此結果暗示語調下降單位也許是一               種認知處理的單位，說 話者在表達一個具有子句結構的概念時，其最後一個語調單位               通常是作為一種增添性的訊息 (added information)，愈到單位的未了，不確性愈低，               所以在訊息的量上就愈多。最後一個語調單位的平均音長會短於第一個語調單位的平均               音長，也部份反應 了不確定性的降低促使說話速度 (articulation rate) 加快。語調               下降單位內的語調單位之間的順序差異也反應在韻律特徵上，最後一個語調單位的語調               下 降程度是最大的，而語調重新提高的程度卻是最小的，整體而言，各各語調單位的               語調下降及語調重新提高的表現是相反的，愈趨後面，語調下降的程度愈大，而愈是               前面的語調單位，其語調重新提高的表現愈強。

                      Abstract                      The thesis acoustically and empirically analyzes two kinds of               prosodic units:  IUs and DUs.  Though they are both prosodically defined,               scant literature concerns with their acoustic properties.  Therefore, our               study aims to acoustically investigate the prosodic features of IUs and               DUs, which are then compared.  Cues characterizing IUs are first discussed               to probe into the issue of why some stretches of speech are difficult to               break into IUs and why some are segmented differently by transcribers.  In               addition to the prosodic phenomena, grammatical structures of DUs are also               investigated, which may provide insights of what the production of a DU               tries to communicate.  Finally, this thesis studies the relationship               between IUs and DUs, including their sizes, grammatical structures and               acoustic behaviors.  Furthermore, how IUs flow within a DU is discussed.                      Two Taiwanese conversations, 26 minutes in total, serve as the data               examined.  Two experiments are performed on the first conversation with the               length of 5 min and 45 sec.  They are designed to answer questions               regarding IUs' prosodic features.  Our results indicate that some acoustic               properties do serve as indicators to IU boundaries.  It is found that               speakers accelerate their speech in the initial of an IU, decelerate it               near the end and then may sometimes remain silent for a while before               initiating anot her IU.  In addition to the change of speech tempo, Fo               movement also characterizes IUs --- they are found to manifest declination               as well as pitch resetting in the beginning.  In the first experiment, the               percentage of transcribers' agreement on IUs' breaking is below 70%.  Two               reasons, individual preference for different cues, together with the               relative importance of these prosodic cues, are examined to account for the               low tendency of agreement.  It is found that one transcriber relies on the               cue of pause much more than others do, while another subject more depends               upon the cue of anacrusis.  On the top of that, when the cues of pause and               final lengthening are not salient enough, people delineate speech               differently.  The results all indicate one thing in common that speech               timing in Taiwanese is relatively more important in serving as the function               of structuring speech.                      The second conversation results in 336 DUs in total.  They show some               prosodic features, as IUs do.  Although DUs are characterized by the same               prosodic features as IUs are, some of these features in DUs are more               prominent than those in IUs.  First, the boundary pauses of DUs are               significantly longer than boundary-within pauses.  Second, Fo development               in DUs is quite different from that in IUs.  DUs show greater extent of               declination and pitch resetting than IUs do.  The results imply that it is               not presenc e or absence of the prosodic features but the magnitude of them               that differentiate DUs from IUs.  Although the two units share acoustic               features with different strength, their realizations in grammatical               structures and their sizes are different.  More than 70% of all DUs are               either simple clauses or clause-complexes, while IUs are phrases or simple               clauses at most.  Their differences in syntactic structures also suggest               the difference in sizes.  On average, a DU contain 11.58 syllables while an               IU 5.68.  On average, a DU is made up of two IUs.  The flowing of IUs               within a DU is found to be unbalanced in terms of the quantity of               information.  The first IU per DU tends to be shorter and contains fewer               syllables than the last IU does.  Nevertheless, one of the results shows a               weighty head phenomon --- syllables in the first IUs are on average longer               than those in the last IUs.  The sequence of IUs also exerts an effect on               prosodic realizations.  The final IUs demonstrate a greater extent of               declination but les s extent of resetting and final lengthening, while the               initial IUs are verbalized with less strength of declination but greater               extent of final lengthening.  In addition to the difference between the               first and last IU of a DU, the first pitch and last pitch of each IU are               also found to decline across the whole DU.                      Keywords:  Intonation, Prosody, Prosodic Units
 國圖紙本論文








